In all seriousness though, this is one of my favorite forums on the board.  Not because everyone's tearing eachother's throat out over who KS'd A_gnoll_00, but because there's a lot of fun discussions and debates that kick off in this forum.<br>
<br>
For the most part, I have all of 1 hobby... EQ.  When I'm not playin it, I like talkin about it, and Soapbox is a great place to do it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Cut through the ranting, and look at the juicy discussions ya got goin on in here...<br>
...effectiveness of shields on non-defense classes.<br>
...possible improvements to the guide/GM program.<br>
...ways to avoid getting ripped off in Bazaar.<br>
...good ways to handle loot distribution in different situations.<br>
...discussion of guildwars, and ways to run them.<br>
...various game-impacting bugs.<br>
...warnings about rez timers and other pitfalls so you can avoid them.<br>
...vegetarianism as a choice in diet or lifestyle.<br>
...politics (whee).<br>
...etc.<br>
<br>
In other words, if you come to this forum, and all you see is bickering and yelling, you're only reading the threads on the most superficial level.  There's a whole lot of informative, interesting, and/or just plain fun stuff that goes on in Soapbox.<br>
<br>
- Syll<br>
